Dear Fulbright Applicant,

This is your final reminder that the application window for the Fulbright
Master's Degree Program (MDP) 2026-27 closes on April 30, 2026.

Programme Overview:
- Sponsor: U.S. Government (USAID / U.S. Embassy Islamabad)
- Destination: United States of America
- Degree: Master's (any accredited U.S. university)
- Funding: Full — tuition, living allowance, health insurance, airfare
- Duration: 1-2 years depending on programme

Eligibility Requirements:
- Pakistani citizen with CNIC
- Bachelor's degree completed or expected by August 2026
- Minimum CGPA: 3.0/4.0 or equivalent
- TOEFL iBT 79+ or IELTS 6.5+ (can be submitted after shortlisting)
- Maximum 4 years of full-time work experience
- Must return to Pakistan after programme

Application Requirements:
- Online application form (completed)
- Statement of Purpose (max 1000 words)
- Three letters of recommendation
- Official academic transcripts
- English test scores

Application Deadline: April 30, 2026 (11:59 PM PST)

Apply now: https://apply.iie.org/fulbright-pak
FAQs and eligibility: https://usefpak.org/fulbright
Webinar recording: https://usefpak.org/info-session-2026

